    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of large tree that grows in swampy soils in the northern U.S. and Canada. It is often cultivated as a shade tree, attractive for fragrant buds thickly coated with an aromatic resin, which is also used to make cough syrups.</Note_Text>
